@node what "What is LowPlay ?"
LowPlay is a small CLI program (7k) that simply plays the following module
formats :

ProTracker (All)
SoundTracker (Most)
NoiseTracker (All)

If your do find one of these that doesn't play, contact @{"me" link ant}.
@endnode

@node req "What do I need to run it?"
An Amiga. I'm not sure what OS version you need.

It works on the following (my machine) :

Amiga A1200 10Mb, 400Mb HD. WB 40.42, Kick 39.106.
@endnode

@node dirlist "What files should I have?"
This distributtion MUST contain :

LowPlay        -   7660   - The main program
LowPlay.guide  -   6423   - The AmigaGuideｮ documentation.
LowPlay.doc    -          - The ASCII documentation.

If any of the files are missing or the incorrect size, contact @{"me" link ant}.

@endnode

@node history "History"

Version v0.90 - Week Beginning 07/04/97
-------------   ---- --------- --------

Began development. Various bugs to do with play-routine. Fixed major timing
problem.

Version v0.99 - 08/04/97
-------------   --------

Fixed command line parsing problem, added dynamic error reporting.
Also fixed yet another timing problem.

Version v1.00 - 09/04/97
-------------   --------

FIRST PUBLIC RELEASE

Improved file loading routine, fixed problem whereby after loading
a module, the program wouldn't allow you to delete the file specified !
Now fixed, but uses more mem (loads everything into buff)
@endnode

