@node use "Using LowPlay"

This must be used from either a CLI (Shell) or a script.
The command accepts the following parameters :

<filename>

Where filename is the name and path of the NT/ST/PT module you wish to play.

If you don't pass a command, the program will display USAGE info.

To quit while playing, press Ctrl-C !

For inclusion into a script, try something like this

LowPlay >NIL: ram:mod.mymodule

This will NOT display any copyright info and play the mod.
@endnode

